cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the behaviour of neural machine translation (NMT) systems. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as NMT systems are a popular application of AI and ML. Additionally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper proposes a soft-attention based technique to make word replacements. Finally, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the proposed technique is an invariance-based adversarial attack on NMT systems, which is similar to adversarial attacks in computer vision.
